description:
This is a 23 minute workout called 'Advanced Breathing - Ultimate Relaxation Exercise | 3 Minute Breath-Hold | Deep Pranayama Relaxation' from the channel Hands-On Meditation.
The workout falls under Rest/Breathing exercises and Rest/Meditation.
It's suitable for Intermediate and Advanced fitness levels.
The workout has a The Deep Recharge and The Zen Flow vibe.
The technique difficulty is Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Increase productivity, performance, and overall well-being while relaxing deeply into this powerful breathing exercise.

This video guides you through the breathing technique at a faster advanced pace - in 5 rounds. You'll be taking 35 Deep Circular Breaths, followed by an Extended Breath-Hold. The Breath-Hold gradually increases each round.

No worries about breathing through your nose or mouth for this exercise. Just do whatever is most comfortable for you.

Round 1-  Breath-Hold  ⏱  1 Minute
Round 2 - Breath-Hold  ⏱  1 Minute 30 Seconds
Round 3 - Breath-Hold  ⏱  2 Minutes
Round 4 - Breath-Hold  ⏱  2 Minute 30 Seconds
Round 5 - Breath-Hold  ⏱  3 Minutes

!!! THE BREATH-HOLD TIMES ARE MEANT ONLY AS A GUIDE - IF YOU FEEL THE URGE TO BREATHE BEFORE THE DESIGNATED TIME - YOU SHOULD GO AHEAD AND TAKE A BREATH !!!

You can also pause the video and extend the Breath-Hold, if you are comfortable. With practice, your breath retention ability will likely increase.
